        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 15 at 6:38PM MDT until June 15 at 7:45PM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>SVRGGW

The National Weather Service in Glasgow has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northeastern Phillips County in northeastern Montana...
Northwestern Valley County in northeastern Montana...

* Until 745 PM MDT.

* At 637 PM MDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 10 miles southeast of Whitewater to 13 miles
southwest of Saco, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage
to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Vandalia, Tampico, Sleeping Buffalo, Hinsdale, The Bentonite Plant,
Bowdoin, and Saco.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

If on or near Nelson and Bowdoin Reservoirs, get away from the water
and move indoors or inside a vehicle. Remember, lightning can strike
out to 15 miles from the parent thunderstorm. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Move to
safe shelter now!  Do not be caught on the water in a thunderstorm.</instruction>
